title: GPs need to 'fundamentally change' to cope with fewer doctors, says top Scottish NHS executive
text: The traditional way in which most local GP practices operate is outdated and needs to “fundamentally change” to cope with the fact that there are now fewer doctors than in the past, one of Scotland’s top NHS executives has said. Elaine
